SIMPLE: bilious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bilious
<hw>Bil"ious</hw> <pr>(b⟦icr⟧l"y⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>biliosus</ets>, fr. <ets>bilis</ets> bile.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to the bile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disordered in respect to the bile; troubled with an
excess of bile; <as>as, a <ex>bilious</ex> patient</as>; dependent on,
or characterized by, an excess of bile; <as>as, <ex>bilious</ex>
symptoms</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Choleric; passionate; ill tempered.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>bilious</xex> old nabob.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bilious temperament</b></col>. <cd>See
<er>Temperament</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biliousness</ent>⟦br⟧
